#---------------------[ BASH PARAMETERS]-------------------#

Parameters = entity storing a value
Variable = parameter with a name

All variables are parameters, but not all parameters are variables.

  examples:
      var_a="Hello World"         :       var_a="Hello World"
      anotehr_var=42              :       another_var=42
      var_a= "Hello World"         :       error
      var_a = "Hello World"       :       error
      var_a ="Hello World"        :       error
      
      
            **  note that a space on any side of the equals sign would return an error. NO SPACES WHEN DECLARING VARIABLES!!  **
            
	    
	    
#-----------------------[	SPECIAL PARAMETERS	]--------------------#

The shell treats several parameters specially. These parameters may only be referenced; assignment to them is not allowed.

source <script> 	and		<file>.script		are both used to run scripts INTERACTIVELY, as opposed to how scripts are typically ran non-interactively.


		special parameter examples:
				
				see day 3 cheat sheet
				
				
				https://git.cybbh.space/programming/bash/public/-/blob/master/Day_3_student_cheat_sheet.adoc
				
				
				
